{"lemma":"جَبّارٌ","slug":"جَبّارٌ","root":"ج.ب.ر","root_slug":"ج-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جَبّار","root":"جبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4951","n4952","n4956","n4957"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"almighty, omnipotent, superhuman"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"mighty, powerful"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"colossal, giant, gigantic, titanic, tremendous, huge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"giant, colossus, Goliath, titan"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tyrant, oppressor, strongman"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَابَرَ (jābara) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Tuesday","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *gabbār-. Compare Hebrew גיבור / גִּבּוֹר (gibbōr) and Classical Syriac ܓܢܒܪܐ (ga(n)bbārā).\n\nAppellative for some martial god, whose name then stood for planets and then like Latin diēs Mārtis or Proto-West Germanic *Tīwas dag after war-gods for Tuesday."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4951","headword_ar":"جُبَارٌ","root":"jbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which no account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which no revenge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retaliation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mulct, is taken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba damahu jubaArFA","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ دَمَهُ جُبَارًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His blood went unrevenged, unretaliated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unexpiated by a mulct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juroHN jubaArN","text_ar":"جُرْحٌ جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wound for which is no retaliation, nor any expiatory mulct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN jubaArN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A war in which is no retaliation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor any expiatory mulct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEodinu jubaArN","text_ar":"المَعْدِنُ جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mine is a thing for which no mulct is exacted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., if the mine fall in upon him who is working in it, and he perish, his hirer is not to be punished for it. (S and Msb from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albiy^oru jubaArN","text_ar":"البِيْرُ جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The well is a thing for which no mulct is exacted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., if a man fall into an ancient well, and perish, his blood is not to be expiated by a mulct: (TA:) or, as some say, it relates to a hired man's descending into a well to cleanse it, or to take forth something from it, if he fall into it and die. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA^r","text_ar":"بار"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jurHu AlEajumaA='i","text_ar":"جُرحُ العَجُمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jubaArN","text_ar":"جُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound of the speechless beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"if it get loose and wound a man or other thing while loose,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a thing for which no retaliation or expiatory mulct is exacted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, * Msb. *) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing: so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA minohu xalaAwapN wujubaArN","text_ar":"اَنَا مِنْهُ خَلَاوَةٌ وُجُبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAlijN","text_ar":"فَالِجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A torrent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that corrupts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mars, and destroys;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so accord. to some copies of the K, and the TA;) as the torrent, &c.: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is corrupted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marred, and destroyed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So accord. to other copies of the K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tuesday;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) an ancient name thereof, (S,) used in the Time of Ignorance; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaArN","text_ar":"جِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n4952","headword_ar":"جِبَارٌ","root":"jbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next precedes."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4956","headword_ar":"جَبَّارٌ","root":"jbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who magnifies himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaves"},{"kind":"page_break","n":375},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proudly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughtily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolently, and does not hold any one to have any claim upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to deserve anything of him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who slays when in anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who slays unjustly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imperious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"domineering, by absolute force and power; overbearing; tyrannical; a tyrant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) any one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who exalts himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is insolent and audacious, in pride and in acts of rebellion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedience; who is bold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"audacious, and immoderate, inordinate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exorbitant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excessively, immoderately,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inordinately, proud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbelieving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedient,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rebel-lious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who exalts himself and is inordinate in infidelity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is extravagant in acts of disobedience and in wrongdoing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averse from obedience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jib~iyrN","text_ar":"جِبِّيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or this latter signifies one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who magnifies himself much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaves very proudly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haughtily"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and the former, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who proudly, haughtily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolently, disdains the service of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jab~aAruwna","text_ar":"جَبَّارُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabaAbirapN","text_ar":"جَبَابِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljab~aArN","text_ar":"الجَبَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of his magnifying Himself [above every other being], (K,) and his highness: (TA:) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Compeller of his creatures to do whatsoever He willeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in lix. 23:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Compeller of his creatures to obey the commands and prohibitions which He pleaseth to impose upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) accord. to Fr, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajobara","text_ar":"اَجْبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the only instance known to him of an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faE~aAlN","text_ar":"فَعَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEala","text_ar":"اَفْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dar~aAkN","text_ar":"دَرَّاكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoraka","text_ar":"اَدْرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, TA:) or, accord. to Fr, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabara","text_ar":"جَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajobara","text_ar":"اَجْبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) it is also explained as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Supreme; the High above his creatures:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Unattainable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence applied to the palm-tree [of which the branches cannot be reached by the hand]: (IAmb, TA:) or it may signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Restorer of the poor to wealth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiency."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) [God is also called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jab~aAru Alquluwbi EalaY fiTaraAtihaA","text_ar":"جَبَّارُ القُلُوبِ عَلَى فِطَرَاتِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Establisher of hearts according to their natural constitutions which He hath given them in the mothers' wombs, disposing them to know Him and to confess Him, both the unfortunate of them and the fortunate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad. of 'Alee.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljawozaA='u","text_ar":"الجَوْزَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the constel-lation Orion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A, K;) because it is [represented] in the form of a crowned king upon a throne. (A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu Aljab~aAri","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ الجَبَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cubit of the king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the long cubit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as Kt thinks, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljb~Ar","text_ar":"الجبّار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here meant a certain foreign king whose fore arm was of full length. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalobN jab~aArN","text_ar":"قَلْبٌ جَبَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heart that receives not admonition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that admits not compassion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jab~aArN","text_ar":"جَبَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Seer, K,) without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Seer, TA,) applied to a palm-tree ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolapN","text_ar":"نَخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall and young;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Seer, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~aArN","text_ar":"جُبَّارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or is applied to palmtrees collectively ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolN","text_ar":"نَخْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall, and above the reach of the hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S;) and the epithet applied to a single palm-tree is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A;) in this sense; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwqN","text_ar":"سَحُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", it signifies a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young"},{"kind":"text","text":"palm-tree,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has attained its utmost height and has borne fruit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has been ascended"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the purpose of cutting off its fruit"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and retains its excellence, surpassing therein other palm-trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, TA.) ―         -b7-  Also, hence, as Az thinks, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Huge, tall, and strong; a giant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, * K.) ―         -b8-  And, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A,) and also without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) applied to a she-camel, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Great"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and fat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","TA","Lh","Msb","Az","IAmb","Seer","M"]},{"entry_id":"n4957","headword_ar":"جُبَّارٌ","root":"jbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jab~aArN","text_ar":"جَبَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}